beer.beer_description:
The second beer in our new bi-monthly IPA series is a nod to the old school, with a Bridge Road twist.

A luminous copper colour in the glass, the aromas are of pineapple, citrus + pine.

Some grapefruit earthiness on the palate, makes way for a firm lingering bitterness and a hint of malt sweetness on the finish.

It’s lean, mean, dank and ready to be drank.

HOPS: Strata, Amarillo, Simcoe, Centennial, Columbus, Warrior
MALT: Ale, Munich, Cara Pils, Light Crystal
YEAST: 1056 American Ale
